episodes.title: Pilot
episodes.plot: A dancer rejected by his homophobic parents and a family man with a high-paying job find themselves being pulled into the world of ball culture in New York in the late 1980s.

episodes.title: Access
episodes.plot: Blanca is denied access to a popular bar leading to a purposeful feud. Meanwhile, inexperienced Damon learns the truth about love and sex when he is asked on a date.

episodes.title: Giving and Receiving
episodes.plot: The House of Evangelista celebrates the holidays and prepares for the Snow Ball in spite of Angel's lack of holiday spirit. Elektra contemplates undergoing an affirming medical procedure.

episodes.title: The Fever
episodes.plot: Candy's insecurities about her appearance are heightened when she is criticized at a ball. Blanca worries when Damon and Ricky have a medical scare that threatens to tear them apart.

episodes.title: Mother's Day
episodes.plot: Blanca is forced to reconnect with her estranged siblings after the death of her mother.

episodes.title: Love Is the Message
episodes.plot: Pray Tell organizes a cabaret for the AIDS ward at a local hospital.

episodes.title: Pink Slip
episodes.plot: Blanca makes a startling revelation about Lil Papi that changes the House of Evangelista forever; Elektra rethinks her means of survival when the House of Abundance is evicted from their apartment.

episodes.title: Mother of The Year
episodes.plot: The ultimate showdown takes place at the Princess Ball, when the House of Evangelista battle against the House of Ferocity and Mother of the Year is decided.
